                        <p style="font-weight:bold; margin-bottom:4px; text-decoration:underline;">Electronic Communications Protocols and Cookies</p>
                        <p>
                            Rosyblue may collect and you consent to the collection of non-personally identifiable information through cookies, web logs, web beacons (also known as action tags) and other monitoring tools. This non-personally identifiable information may be used for better understanding and improving the usability, performance and effectiveness of the Web Site and marketing initiatives. We may share or transfer non-personally identifiable information with or to our affiliates, licensees and partners. Where authorized by us, third parties may use cookies, Rosyblue's web log files, web beacons and other monitoring technologies to compile, aggregate statistics on Rosyblue's behalf.
                            Cookies
                        </p>
                        <p>"Cookies" are pieces of data or text files that are sent by a web server that are saved by your internet browser and stored on your computer. Use of cookies is industry standard and information contained in cookies will enhance your experience on the Site. Cookies are used to analyze web page flow, evaluate promotions, deliver you a personalized shopping experience, track visits from our partners/affiliates and allow the use of our shopping cart. Cookies contain information that can later be read by a web server in the domain that issued the cookie to you. Rosyblue does not use cookies to collect or store any personal information, but they may be tied to the personal information you knowingly choose to provide to us.</p>
                        <p>
                            We may use two types of cookies - session cookies and persistent cookies - to enable us to collect aggregate information on the usage patterns of the Site, such as what areas of the Site are visited most often, so that we can tailor the Site to user preferences. Session cookies exist only for as long as your Internet browser remains open. When the session ends, the Internet browser is closed and the cookies go away. Persistent cookies, in contrast, last from visit to visit. Persistent cookies are saved on a visitor’s computer by the Internet browser and do not go away when you exit your Internet browser.
                            You have control over cookies. Most Internet browsers can be set to refuse to accept cookies, although this may affect your Internet experience, including your use of the Site. You can also erase cookies that are already on your computer, block all cookies or receive a warning before a cookie is stored. Please refer to your Internet browser instructions or “help” screen to learn more about these functions. If you choose to have your Internet browser refuse cookies, the Site may not function properly for you.
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-weight:bold; margin-bottom:4px; text-decoration:underline;">Embedded Pixels/ Web Beacons</p>
                        <p>The Web Site’s pages may also contain embedded electronic images or pixel technologies, commonly referred to as web beacons. These web beacons allow Rosyblue to track the number of users who have visited the Web Site’s pages and may also be used to assist in delivering cookies on the Web Site. In addition, we may also include beacons in our e-mail messages in order to track whether the message has been opened or acted upon.</p>
                        <p style="font-weight:bold; margin-bottom:4px; text-decoration:underline;">Embedded URLs</p>
                        <p>Rosyblue may also use a tracking technique that employs embedded URLs to allow use of the Site without cookies. Embedded URLs allow limited information to follow you as you navigate the Site, but is not associated with personal information and is not used beyond the session.</p>
